# CODEOWNERS for satus.sh
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews on pull requests. Even
# with a single maintainer today, declaring ownership signals process
# maturity to acquirers and keeps the door open for additional reviewers
# without restructuring later.
#
# Syntax: <path-pattern>  <owner>
# Owners are GitHub usernames or teams (prefixed with the org name).

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                           @passkeybridge

# Critical surfaces. Keep these explicit so they survive a future
# wildcard relaxation.
/src/routes/api/            @passkeybridge
/src/lib/                   @passkeybridge
/supabase/migrations/       @passkeybridge
/src/integrations/          @passkeybridge

# Legal, security, and licensing artifacts.
/LICENSE                    @passkeybridge
/SECURITY.md                @passkeybridge
/CODEOWNERS                 @passkeybridge
